            <h1>Engineering</h1>
<p>the branch of science and technology concered with the design,building,and use of engines,machines,and structure</p>
<img src="og-yoe.jpg">
<h2><u>Departments of engineering</h2></u>
<ul><li>Mechanical Engineering</li><li>Civil engineering </li><li>Electrical engineering</li><li>Communiation Engineering</li></ul>
<h2>Mechanical Engineering:</h2>
<p> comprises the design and analysis of heat and mechanical power for the operation of machines and mechanical systems.

</p>
<h2>Civil engineering:</h2>
<P> comprises the design, construction and maintenance of the physical and natural built environments.</p>
<h2>Electrical engineering:</h2>
<p>Electrical engineering comprises the study and application of electricity, electronics and electromagnetism.
</p>
<h2>Communiation Engineering:</h2>
<p>The creation of physical devices and abstract methods that make it possible to conduct electricity.</p>
